column5: Had time for a nice midday diversion. So I grabbed the pack and a couple of rods and away we go. Nothing spectacular, but enough to keep me entertained.
Nice mix of fish!!  I think you foul hooked the pike?
That's where the tear in the upper lip ends.
Man, I cant wait to retire like you! Thats in my back yard and I cant seem to get out much this year. Great haul out of there!
It beats doing chores and getting nagged.  I still go to St Jacobs once or twice a week to flog produce and I'm still making tackle, But those are fun things.
Right on Bruce Got to love those mid day diversions!!! Good job.... Keep it up and thanks for sharing Jacques
